ide of the medal places with one round remaining at Saint-Denis' packed-out Aquatics Centre.\", \"from\": 207, \"to\": 416, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Harper\", \"from\": 207, \"to\": 213}, {\"ngram\": \"Mew Jensen\", \"from\": 218, \"to\": 228}, {\"ngram\": \"a superb start\", \"from\": 240, \"to\": 254}, {\"ngram\": \"their opening dive\", \"from\": 280, \"to\": 298}, {\"ngram\": \"the medal places\", \"from\": 331, \"to\": 347}, {\"ngram\": \"one round\", \"from\": 353, \"to\": 362}, {\"ngram\": \"Saint-Denis' packed-out Aquatics Centre\", \"from\": 376, \"to\": 415}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, a slip-up fromAustralia's duo of Maddison Keeney and Anabelle Smith saw the British pair finish third and pick up the bronze medal, withChinaand the USA taking gold and silver respectively.\", \"from\": 418, \"to\": 616, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 460, \"end\": 475, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maddison_Keeney\", \"score\": 0.9999999320498342, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Maddison Keeney\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maddison_Keeney\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maddison_Keeney\"}, {\"begin\": 503, \"end\": 510, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9392258688011711, \"rank\": 0.0332156186015661, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 576, \"end\": 579, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9954599291114163, \"rank\": 0.004369517509530289, \"text\": \"USA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a slip-up fromAustralia's duo\", \"from\": 427, \"to\": 456}, {\"ngram\": \"Anabelle Smith\", \"from\": 480, \"to\": 494}, {\"ngram\": \"the bronze medal\", \"from\": 541, \"to\": 557}, {\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 587, \"to\": 591}, {\"ngram\": \"silver\", \"from\": 596, \"to\": 602}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The joy and relief was written all over the faces of both Harper and Mew Jensen as they successfully secured Britain's first female Olympic diving medal in 64 years.\", \"from\": 618, \"to\": 783, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 727, \"end\": 734, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9028871627190023, \"rank\": 0.10752953443214174, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The joy\", \"from\": 618, \"to\": 625}, {\"ngram\": \"relief\", \"from\": 630, \"to\": 636}, {\"ngram\": \"the faces\", \"from\": 658, \"to\": 667}, {\"ngram\": \"both Harper\", \"from\": 671, \"to\": 682}, {\"ngram\": \"Mew Jensen\", \"from\": 687, \"to\": 697}, {\"ngram\": \"64 years\", \"from\": 774, \"to\": 782}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After standing on the podium to collect their medals, the Team GB stars spoke with BBC Sport, giving their reaction after a rollercoaster competition in the French capital.\", \"from\": 785, \"to\": 957, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 868, \"end\": 877, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC_Sport\", \"score\": 0.9402817370051462, \"rank\": 0.06346450813501708, \"text\": \"BBC Sport\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC_Sport\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC_Sport\"}, {\"begin\": 942, \"end\": 948, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.729527616027548, \"rank\": 0.3327362437965026, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": 